Package: ferrite
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ferrite-cli
Suggests: ferrite-tui
Description: High-performance, tiered-storage key-value store
 Ferrite is a Redis-compatible key-value store with tiered storage
 support. It provides the speed of memory, the capacity of disk,
 and the economics of cloud.
 .
 Features:
  * Drop-in Redis replacement with 99% command compatibility
  * Tiered storage (memory, SSD, cloud)
  * Vector search and embeddings
  * Time-series data support
  * Graph database capabilities
  * CRDT support for distributed systems
  * Built-in RAG and semantic caching
 .
 This package contains the Ferrite server.

Package: ferrite-cli
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Command-line interface for Ferrite
 This package contains the Ferrite command-line interface (ferrite-cli),
 a Redis-compatible REPL for interacting with Ferrite servers.

Package: ferrite-tui
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: ferrite
Description: Terminal UI dashboard for Ferrite
 This package contains the Ferrite Terminal User Interface (ferrite-tui),
 a real-time dashboard for monitoring Ferrite servers.
